\"sample_id\":\"Ababon-Sample-032126-01\",\"ref_no\":\"REF-SMLPHK\",\"submitted_by\":\"kentoi\",\"date_submitted\":\"2026-03-23 00:00:00\",\"date_analyzed\":\"2026-03-20 00:00:00\",\"lab_no\":\"lab1\",\"field_no\":\"field 1\",\"ph_level\":\"10.1\",\"organic_matter\":\"8\",\"nitrogen\":\"9\",\"phosphorus\":\"7.9\",\"potassium\":\"8.1\",\"recommendation\":\"SOIL ANALYSIS RECOMMENDATION REPORT\\nSource: Bureau of Soils & Water Management (BSWM) \\\/ FAO Soil Interpretation Guidelines\\n==========================================================================================\\nCrop     : Coffee - Arabica\\nSoil Type: Clay\\n==========================================================================================\\n\\n1. SOIL CONDITION ASSESSMENT\\n+----------------------+------------+-----------+------------------------------------------------------+\\n| Parameter            | Value      | Rating    | Remarks                                              |\\n+----------------------+------------+-----------+------------------------------------------------------+\\n| Soil pH              | 10.1       | Very High | Strongly alkaline. Major correction needed.          |\\n| Organic Matter       | 8%         | Very High | Excellent. Avoid excess manure\\\/compost.              |\\n| Nitrogen (N)         | 9%         | Very High | Excess. No nitrogen fertilizer needed.               |\\n| Phosphorus (P)       | 7.9 ppm    | Low       | Deficient. Apply 40-60 kg P2O5\\\/ha (banded).          |\\n| Potassium (K)        | 8.1 ppm    | Very Low  | Severely deficient. Apply 60-90 kg K2O\\\/ha.           |\\n+----------------------+------------+-----------+------------------------------------------------------+\\n\\n2. FERTILIZER RECOMMENDATION\\n   (Note: full application timing is in Section 4 below)\\n+-----------------+--------------------------------------+--------------------+----------------------+\\n| Nutrient        | Fertilizer Product                   | Rate (per ha)      | When to Apply        |\\n+-----------------+--------------------------------------+--------------------+----------------------+\\n| Nitrogen (N)    | None required                        | Do not apply       | Risk of N leaching   |\\n| Phosphorus (P)  | Solophos (0-18-0) or Complete (14-14 | 40-60 kg P2O5\\\/ha   | At planting, banded  |\\n| Potassium (K)   | Muriate of Potash (0-0-60) or SOP (0 | 60-90 kg K2O\\\/ha    | Split 2x (see Sec. 4 |\\n+-----------------+--------------------------------------+--------------------+----------------------+\\n\\n3. SOIL AMENDMENT\\n+------------------------+------------------------------------+--------------+--------------------------+\\n| Concern                | Product                            | Rate         | When to Apply            |\\n+------------------------+------------------------------------+--------------+--------------------------+\\n| pH Correction (Alkalin | Elemental Sulfur + Gypsum          | 1-3 t\\\/ha     | Immediately \\u2014 multi-seas |\\n+------------------------+------------------------------------+--------------+--------------------------+\\n\\n4. APPLICATION SCHEDULE SUMMARY\\n+----------------------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------+\\n| When                       | Action \\\/ What to Do                                                  |\\n+----------------------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------+\\n| IMMEDIATELY                | Apply Elemental Sulfur to lower high soil pH.                        |\\n| At planting                | Apply phosphorus fertilizer near root zone (banded).                 |\\n| At planting (basal)        | Apply 50% of potassium fertilizer.                                   |\\n| 1-2 months after planting  | Apply remaining 50% potassium (top-dress).                           |\\n| Every year                 | Apply organic matter (compost\\\/manure) to maintain soil health.       |\\n| Every 6-12 months          | Re-test soil to evaluate progress and update fertilizer plan.        |\\n+----------------------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------+\\n\\n5. GOOD FARMING PRACTICES\\n  * Mulch around coffee plants with dried leaves or rice straw (5-10 cm thick).\\n  * Keep crop residues on the field after harvest -- do NOT burn them.\\n  * Plant legume cover crops during fallow season to naturally add nitrogen.\\n  * Avoid deep plowing to protect soil structure and organic matter.\\n  * Never apply fertilizer on extremely dry or waterlogged soil.\\n  * Always wash hands after handling fertilizers and chemicals.\\n\\n==========================================================================================\\nIMPORTANT REMINDERS\\n==========================================================================================\\n  ! ALWAYS correct soil pH FIRST -- fertilizers do not work on wrong pH.\\n  ! SPLIT nitrogen and potassium -- never apply the full dose at once.\\n  ! RE-TEST your soil every 6-12 months after major amendments.\\n  ! BANDED application of phosphorus near roots is more efficient than broadcasting.\\n==========================================================================================\",\"validation_status\":\"pending\",\"expert_comments\":null,\"validated_by_name\":null},{\"s\":\"arr\"}]],{\"s\":\"arr\"}],\"defaultAction\":null,\"defaultActionArguments\":null,\"componentFileAttachments\":[[],{\"s\":\"arr\"}],\"areFormStateUpdateHooksDisabledForTesting\":false,\"mountedFormComponentActions\":[[],{\"s\":\"arr\"}],\"mountedFormComponentActionsArguments\":[[],{\"s\":\"arr\"}],\"mountedFormComponentActionsData\":[[],{\"s\":\"arr\"}],\"mountedFormComponentActionsComponents\":[[],{\"s\":\"arr\"}],\"mountedInfolistActions\":[[],{\"s\":\"arr\"}],\"mountedInfolistActionsData\":[[],{\"s\":\"arr\"}],\"mountedInfolistActionsComponent\":null,\"mountedInfolistActionsInfolist\":null,\"isTableLoade